P2P Communication:
==================

   * message format
      - header

     0   4          16   20          32
     +---+-----------+---+------------+
     |ver|   flags   |ToM| reserved   |
     +---+-----------+----------------+
     |         payload length         |
     +--------------------------------+
     |     128 bit source address     |
     +--------------------------------+
     |   128 bit destination address  |
     +--------------------------------+

       - fields:
           ver: 4 bit version information
	        current version: 0x1
	   flags: 12 bit not yet specified
	   ToM: type of message
	             - 0xxx user data
		     - 1xxx system message
		     - 1000 hello packet
           reserved: 12 bit not yet specified
	   payload length: 32bit describing the length of payload in bytes
	   source: 128bit source descriptor
	   destination: 128bit destination descriptor

peer_t ("name-of-peer", listen-url, cookie);

   * connection initiation  process:

       - on connect the client side sends a HELO packet (ToM: 0x8) to the server
         to indicate who is connecting

   * the peer can communicate with all other peers sharing the same cookie
